               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa nәfq “Book of the Assistant Priest” (fols. 3ra-31rb) &#xD;
                     I-1) Prayer by the assistant priest receiving the host during the Prothesis
                     (fol.3ra-3va, l. 1): excerpt from the Liturgy of Catechumen (MQ, Śәrʿatä
                     qәddase, ch. III, §§ 23-25) &#xD; I-2) Prayer of oblation (fols. 3va l.1-5ra
                     l.6): excerpt from the Liturgy of Catechumen (MQ, Śәrʿatä qәddase, ch. III, §§
                     41-44.) &#xD; I-3) Fәtḥat za-wald “Absolution of the Son” (fols. 5ra l.6-7vb
                     l.8): excerpt from the Liturgy of Catechumen (MQ, Śәrʿatä qәddase, ch. III, §§
                     56-60). &#xD; I-4) General absolution (fols. 7vb l.8-10ra l.5): excerpt from
                     the Liturgy of Catechumen (MQ, Śәrʿatä qәddase, ch. III, §§ 61-65). &#xD; I-5)
                     Concluding chant after the reading from the Pauline Epistles (fols. 10ra
                     l.6-11va l.6): excerpt from the Liturgy of the Word (MQ, Śәrʿatä qәddase, ch.
                     III, §§ 132-135). &#xD; I-6) Universal prayer by the assistant priest (fols.
                     11va l.7-16vb l.8): excerpt from the Liturgy of the Word (MQ, Śәrʿatä qәddase,
                     ch. III, §§ 194-211). &#xD; I-7) Prayers to be recited while entering the
                     church (fols.16vb l.8-18va l.2): excerpt from the Liturgy of the Word (MQ,
                     Śәrʿatä qәddase, ch. IV §§ 6-12).&#xD; I-8) Supplication for peace, the
                     hierarchy and the assembly (fols. 18va l.3-21ra l.12): excerpt from the Liturgy
                     of the Word (MQ, Śәrʿatä qәddase, ch. IV, §§ 15-21). &#xD; I-9) Supplication
                     for the congregation (fols. 21rb l.1-22vb l.7): excerpt from the Liturgy of the
                     Word (MQ, Śәrʿatä qәddase, ch. IV, §§ 21-30).&#xD; I-10) Prayer of blessing of
                     St Basil (fols. 22vb l.8-26rb l.11): excerpt from the Liturgy of the Eucharist,
                     Anaphora of the Apostles (MQ, Qәddase za-ḥawāryāt, §§ 10-21). &#xD; I-11)
                     Prayer of intercession following the imposition of the celebrant‘s hand (fols.
                     26rb l.11-30rb l.11): excerpt from the Liturgy of the Eucharist, Anaphora of
                     the Apostles (MQ, Qәddase za-ḥawāryāt, §§ 154-158).&#xD; I-12) Prayer to be
                     read instead of Prayer of Benediction (fols. 30va l.1-31rb l.12): excerpt from
                     the Liturgy of St Gregory (MQ, Qәddase Gorgoryos, §§ 55-59).</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
